{"actual_usd":0.12483,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":169,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24459,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I dust my hands on my apron and lean one hip against the counter, the oven warmth at my side making me answer a little more plainly.* \"When folks say 'ransom,' I think they're reaching for the costliness of it, not picturing the devil standing there with his hand out.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through.* \"I'd put it this way: Jesus gave himself to save us from sin and death and the judgment we were under before God. So if there's a 'who' in it at all, it isn't Satan getting paid off like some proper owner. It's more that Christ satisfies what justice required and frees us by his own sacrifice. Satan loses in that story— he doesn't profit from it.\"\n\n\"What brought that question on?\"","rolling_24h_usd":53.53018000000002,"run_id":"77639f2c-a0ea-4401-b115-e64403e8c06e"}
